#Instructions

Username: Diego
Password: Changeme123

Follow hololens setup guide
https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/holographic/documentation
>
https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/holographic/install_the_tools
>
https://github.com/drv14/Research2016

Clone or Download> Download ZIP

Extract ZIP

open your Unity for HoloLens and open project tothe project file

It will build the project

When it opens>

File > Build Settings > Windows Store >

Put scene "Main" at the top if it is not already

SDK: Universal 10
UWP Build Type: D3D
Build and Run on: Local Machine

Click "player settings" which should open up in the inspector
Player Settings>
Click "settings for Windows Store" icon if its not already selected

Other Settings>
Check Virtual Reality Supported and Virtual Reality SDKs should say Windows Holographic

Publishing Settings>
Check Internet Client, Microphone, SpatialPerception

Back on the "File> build settings" pop-up" click "Build"

Make a new folder named "Builds"
Select Folder "Builds"

Browse to Research2016/Builds/PsychProj2016.sln and open it

Note: Visual Studio must be set up following the instructions found here>

https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/holographic/using_visual_studio

Change it to 

Release - x86 - Remote Machine/Device

(Remote Machine will need the IP, Device if the lens is plugged in)

Run

Note: Visual Studio must be set up following the instructions found here>

https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/holographic/using_visual_studio
